commText: Ishan Kishan and Rohit are at the crease. Ishan Kishan is on strike. Williams will open the attack
Williams to Ishan Kishan, no run, tight back of a length delivery on off, neat back foot block
Williams to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, full and swinging into the stumps, driven wide of mid-wicket
Williams to Rohit, wide, full and down leg, Rohit flicks and misses, wide called. This one is clocked at 148kph
Williams to Rohit, 2 runs, Rohit is very lucky, the top-edge clears Pant and JFM running back. A short of length delivery and hurries Rohit on the pull, he was turning his head away as he pulled
Now a kite on the field stops play. Rohit gives it to Pant who hands it to the square leg ump.
Williams to Rohit, no run, full outside off, Rohit gets forward to defend to cover
Williams to Rohit, no ball, the extra pace of Williams is troubling Rohit, he gives the charge and it hits the bat high and dribbles to mid-on but Williams has overstepped
A free-hit to Rohit.
Williams to Rohit, no run, wide of the crease and angled in full on the stumps, Rohit flicks and misses, rushed past the bat, smashed into the pad

Williams to Rohit, 5 wides, poor delivery, down leg, Rohit pulls and it flies wide of the diving Pant to his left, initially given as runs and then they change it to wides, big deviation as Rohit missed the shot and the ball swung away from the diving Pant

Williams to Rohit, FOUR, full and angling into middle, Rohit flicks and it's off the thick inside half, wide of mid-wicket, Khaleel from deep mid-wicket gets across and the leg was in contact with the cushions, when he pushed the ball back, so four. Sloppy from Khaleel on the slide
Khaleel Ahmed, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, leg byes, 1 run, short of length and angling into the pads, Ishan Kishan flicks and misses, a legbye taken
Khaleel Ahmed to Rohit, 1 run, fullish outside off, square-driven to deep backward point
Rohit 1033 runs vs DC, goes past 1030 runs by Kohli
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, superb shot. Full and angling into leg-stump, Ishan Kishan walks and whips that wide of mid-on

Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, that's lucky. Ishan Kishan smiles. Full just outside off, he drives and the thick outside-edge flies wide of Pant, to the keeper's left, no chance of catching that as it was well wide
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, full outside off, Ishan Kishan stands and delivers. Smashed it straight down the ground. Hat-trick of fours
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, very full on the stumps, driven to mid-on and Ishan Kishan retains the strike with that run
Williams to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, slower ball off-cutter just outside off, Ishan Kishan pulls over mid-wicket and no chance for deep square leg to his right
Williams to Ishan Kishan, no run, 147.6kph, fullish on middle, Ishan Kishan pushes and it's a thick inside-edge on to the pad, dribbles to the off-side
Williams to Ishan Kishan, no run, a low full-toss and Ishan Kishan is surprised as it dips on him slightly, flicked to mid-wicket
Williams to Ishan Kishan, no run, does not stick and the chance goes. Full on the stumps, drilled at Williams who sticks his right hand out and down it goes
That has stung Williams, so the physio is out there.
Williams to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, slower ball short dug in, Ishan Kishan pulls to deep mid-wicket
Williams to Rohit, 1 run, the attempted yorker on the stumps is a low full-toss, Rohit makes room and drives wide of extra-cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Rohit, out Caught by Shai Hope!! Rohit falls early. Did not look like getting any runs today to be honest. Was scratchy right from ball one and now in trying to clear mid-off falls. Full outside off, he slices across the ball and Hope takes an easy catch to his left. Rohit c Shai Hope b Khaleel Ahmed 8(8) [4s-1]
MI bring SKY as their impact player. Thushara out.
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, a slower ball off-cutter on a back of a length outside off, Suryakumar Yadav gets forward to push to mid-off

Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, SKY has started. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, he brings out the wristy trademark whip and it sails over deep backward square leg. Pant wants Khaleel Ahmed to bang it in
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, slower ball full outside off, Suryakumar Yadav now lofts over extra-cover and mid-off, just clears them
Rohit Sharma vs Khaleel Ahmed 39 balls 28 runs Two dismissals SR 71.79
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, byes, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter and angling away from Suryakumar Yadav who again tries to send it to leg, misses, Pant can't stop it and it's a bye
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, slower ball full on the stumps, Ishan Kishan flicks through square leg
Mukesh Kumar, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Axar!! Mukesh Kumar strikes first ball. A hard back of a length on the stumps, Ishan Kishan walks and tries to slash across the ball, miscues it and Axar at mid-off jogs back to take a simple catch. DC well on top. Ishan Kishan c Axar b Mukesh Kumar 20(14) [4s-4]
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, short of length on the stumps, defended in front of mid-off for a quick single
Mukesh Kumar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, fine yorker on the stumps, Suryakumar Yadav digs it out
Mukesh Kumar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Suryakumar Yadav finds extra-cover with a drive
Mukesh Kumar to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, slower ball leg-cutter and it's down leg, easy for Suryakumar Yadav who helps it to the fine-leg fence
Mukesh Kumar to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, this slower ball off-cutter outside off sits up and Suryakumar Yadav cuts wide of backward point, poor bowling

Over Summary (1-5 overs) -- Williams starts off with a 14-run over -- Ishan smashes Khaleel for a hat-trick of fours -- Williams drops a tough caught and bowled off Ishan -- Khaleel strikes and Rohit departs cheaply -- SKY gets off the mark with a six -- Mukesh strikes with his first ball, Ishan gone -- MI bring up their 50 in 4.5 overs
Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 1 run, short of length on off, Tilak Varma defends and the thick outside-edge runs down to third man
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Suryakumar Yadav gets forward to punch to extra-cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, one-handed six to fine-leg. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, Suryakumar Yadav loses his bottom-hand but still has enough
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, slower ball off-cutter wide again, Suryakumar Yadav drives straight to the fielder at extra-cover
Khaleel Ahmed round the wicket.
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, was a wide had Suryakumar Yadav left it, instead he reaches for it and slices the drive, wide of Pant and short third man
Khaleel Ahmed back over the wicket.
Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Williams!! Khaleel Ahmed has the last laugh. The slower ball off-cutter does it. Did it hold up on Suryakumar Yadav a bit? He gets forward and checks his punch, a dolly to cover. SKY stands there chewing his gum disappointed, he can't believe that he has found the man. Massive wicket and MI in trouble now. Also the timeout. Suryakumar Yadav c Williams b Khaleel Ahmed 26(13) [4s-3 6s-2]
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Yadav, comes into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, 1 run, flat and outside the leg-stump, Tilak Varma goes on the back foot to whip to the leg-side
A slip for Hardik Pandya.
Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, the googly on a good length on off, punched wide of point
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fraction short and turning away from outside off, Tilak Varma punches to sweeper cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, the orthodox leggie and Hardik Pandya punches to wide long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, wide, way outside off, left alone to take the wide
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, 1 run, down leg, nudged to deep backward square leg
Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, googly and on a good length on off, punched to long-off
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Axar to Hardik Pandya, no run, flat and full on off, Hardik Pandya drives to mid-off
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, fullish and angling into the stumps, Hardik Pandya mistimes the drive to long-on
Axar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, good length and on off, Tilak Varma whips it to deep mid-wicket
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, flat good length on off, punched to long-off
Axar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fraction short outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Axar to Hardik Pandya, SIX, tossed up and Hardik Pandya has nailed this straight down the ground, he gets forward and gets all of it, that should give him confidence
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, 1 run, flat good length outside off, cut to sweeper cover

Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, Williams at deep backward square leg did not pick that, was a chance. Tossed up outside the leg-stump, Hardik Pandya sweeps and Williams did not judge it, bounces in front of him and he can't stop it either, Kuldeep Yadav not happy at all
Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, bad ball, tossed up down leg, easy with short fine-leg in, Hardik Pandya sweeps to the deep backward square leg fence

Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, hat-trick of fours. Dubey the sub did so well at sweeper cover, runs and dives to his right but palms it and the ball hits the cushions, Hardik Pandya goes on the back foot and smashed the cut wide of extra-cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, no run, this is a seam-up back of a length dart on the stumps, Hardik Pandya pushes to extra-cover

Kuldeep Yadav to Hardik Pandya, SIX, Hardik Pandya has found his touch back. Was short and turning back in, he goes on the back foot and smears it flat and wide of long-on, that was a skimmer of a hit
DC now have their impact sub - Rasikh Dar in.
Axar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, flat and turns back in from good length, Tilak Varma wrists it to deep mid-wicket
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, flat good length on off, Hardik Pandya cuts to sweeper cover
Axar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fullish outside off, Tilak Varma shuffles across to sweep and misses, struck outside off
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, pushed down to long-on
Axar to Tilak Varma, SIX, just clears Hope at long-on. A good length delivery outside off, Tilak Varma hacks and did not get all of it, enough to clear Hope
Axar to Tilak Varma, FOUR, fullish outside off and now Tilak Varma turns around to reverse-sweep it over short third man, nearly all the way, one bounce over the ropes

Over Summary (6-10 overs) -- SKY hits a four and a six off Khaleel but falls in the same over -- MI finish the powerplay with 65/3 -- Hardik breaks the shackles by launching Axar for a six -- Kuldeep v Hardik - 4, 4, 4, 0, 6 -- MI bring up their 100 in 9 overs -- Tilak smashes a four and a six off Axar
Rasikh Dar Salam, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, wide, starts with a bouncer that is too short and too high, Hardik ignores and it is signalled a wide for height
Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Hardik punches it on the rise to sweeper cover
Round the wicket to Tilak
Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, 1 run, I0$ yorker on off-stump, Tilak digs it out to mid-off

Delhi review! Rasikh Salam was very confident in his caught behind appeal. Pant also says "mein bhi kuch suna (even I heard something)" and reviews. There's clear daylight between bat and ball. Nothing on UltraEdge either. Not Out

Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, no run, Delhi lose a review. Hardik will feel missed out there. On a length and outside off, he had the width to free his arms and goes hard on the slash, gets beaten and the ball missed the edge comfortably
Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, very full delivery at the stumps, Hardik toe-ends the drive to long-on
Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, 1 run, I0$ slower ball outside off, Tilak cracks it square and the sweeper tidies up
Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, no run, another freebie that Hardik has missed out. Full toss outside off, he throws his bat on the drive and does not connect
Mukesh Kumar [1.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Tilak Varma, leg byes, 1 run, I0$ delivery that cramps the southpaw, Tilak cannot connect with his heave and is struck on the body,

Mukesh Kumar to Hardik Pandya, SIX, no missing out this time. This is a gift from Mukesh - he attempts a slower ball but drags it down, sits up nicely for Hardik and he nails the pull over wide long-on
Pant goes all the way to have a word with Mukesh. There's a fly slip and a total of three men behind square on the off-side inside the ring
Mukesh Kumar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, low full toss around off, Hardik drives to long-off
Mukesh Kumar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, low full toss on the pads, Tilak flicks to deep square leg
Mukesh Kumar to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, full toss outside off, Hardik saw that and threw his bat on the big shot, the bottom hand comes off the bat handle and he ends up slicing it over backward point
Mukesh Kumar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, fullish delivery close to off, Hardik drills it to long-on and retains strike

Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, in the air and safe. Low full toss and Hardik can't quite get under it, he miscues the loft and the ball goes straight up, luckily for him it lands inside the ring near the mid-on region
Round the wicket to Tilak
Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, 1 run, speared full on leg-stump, Tilak whips it towards deep mid-wicket
Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Mukesh Kumar!! The impact sub makes an impact. The partnership has been broken and Hardik is sent on his way. It was the back of the hand slower ball and it completely deceived the MI skipper, he was through the shot early and miscued it towards the point region, Mukesh settles under it and manages to hang on. Hardik's best knock of the season and he falls four short of a fifty. Hardik Pandya c Mukesh Kumar b Rasikh Salam 46(24) [4s-4 6s-3]
Nehal Wadhera, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rasikh Salam to Nehal Wadhera, FOUR, that's a gift. Full toss on leg-stump, Wadhera gets inside the line and helps it along the way to fine leg
Rasikh Salam to Nehal Wadhera, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Nehal Wadhera, out Caught by Pant!! Rasikh has a knack of picking wickets and he's got two in one over. Short stay for Wadhera today. On a length and around off, Wadhera tries to steer it to third man but it was too close to him, guides it low to Pant and he takes a good sharp catch bending forward. Nehal Wadhera c Pant b Rasikh Salam 4(2) [4s-1]
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rasikh Salam to Tim David, 1 run, I0$ short of length around off, David knocks it to cover and gets off the mark
Khaleel Ahmed [3.0-0-34-2] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, 1 run, shuffled across and showed his cards early, Khaleel angled it outside off and David had to adjust, chops it to backward point and settles with a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fullish delivery on off, Tilak drives to long-on
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, 1 run, I0$ slower ball outside off, David throws his bat and slices it to deep backward point
Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 1 run, short and bowled into the wicket, Tilak waits and slaps it to sweeper cover

Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, SIX, smashed! David walks across his stumps, gets under the slower ball and launches it over cow corner. A spectator tries to take the catch but gets hit on the face instead. He seems to be bleeding and is being escorted out by the security guard. That's unfortunate and hope it is not too serious
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, 1 run, short of length outside off, David pulls to deep mid-wicket and retains strike
Kuldeep Yadav [2.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Tim David, 1 run, googly around leg-stump, David flicks to deep square leg
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, SIX, fraction short and Tilak is quick to pounce, he crouches low and pulls it to deep square leg. Just manages to clear the rope. He needs to step it up now..
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, no run, slower and turning away, Tilak slaps it straight to extra cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, FOUR, seam-up quicker delivery bowled at I0$, Tilak heaves it between deep mid-wicket and long-on, Stubbs gets across to the ball but cannot make the stop
Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, FOUR, Kuldeep was brought back for David but it is Tilak who is taking him apart. He takes this on the full and reverse sweeps it past a diving backward point

Kuldeep Yadav to Tilak Varma, SIX, 21 from the over and MI are still alive. This is floated up and Tilak does not need a second invitation at this stage, he pounces on it and thumps it way over the long-off fence
Summary (Overs 11-15) > Rasikh bowls a very tight over > Rasikh returns to pick up two in an over > Tilak and David keep MI going with some big hits > Tilak takes Kuldeep’s over for 21
Lizaad Williams [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Williams to Tim David, 1 run, miscue and David is lucky that the ball didn't carry to long-on, goes on the bounce to Stubbs

Williams to Tilak Varma, FOUR, fifty for Tilak. He gets there off 25 balls. Another game where he has gone about his business in a calm manner. Took a back seat when Hardik was blazing away and now has taken the front seat. Slower short ball around leg, he pulls it just wide of short fine and gets the boundary
Williams to Tilak Varma, 2 wides, backs away and Williams tries to follow him, Tilak moves inside the line and lets the ball pass, Pant dives to his right and parries it away, couple of extras
Williams to Tim David, 1 run, I0$ fullish delivery in the slot, David drags the heave to long-on
Seems like an issue with the ball. But the umpires are satisified and Williams will continue with the same
Williams to Tilak Varma, 1 run, very full delivery on leg-stump, Tilak ekes out an inside edge backward of square leg
Williams to Tim David, FOUR, another delivery right in the slot and David does not miss out - full pitcher outside off, he thumps it flat over extra cover and the ball bounces just inside the rope
Williams to Tim David, 1 run, full delivery on off, David whips it to deep mid-wicket and has to be content with a single

Timeout! 71 needed from 24 balls. You'd think the bowling team has the upper hand but this season has shown us some crazy things happening during this period. Still anybody's game. Who are the bowlers left? Rasikh has a couple, Williams has one and Mukesh has a couple, so Pant has options. For MI, there's still Nabi to come after this pair, so they still have batting left. This game too will be going down to the wire
Rasikh Dar Salam [2.0-0-12-2] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Tim David, wide, looks for the wide yorker but sprays it too far outside off, David ignores
Rasikh Salam to Tim David, wide, now tries the bouncer but it is too high, David watches it sail over him and it is called a wide for height
Rasikh Salam to Tim David, 1 run, I0$ full and at the stumps, David drives to long-on and brings up the 50-run stand

Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, no run, premeditated and missed out on a juicy full toss, it was at a nice height outside off but Tilak had committed to play the lap, he was on his knee and couldn't adjust quickly to play the reverse lap/scoop
Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, 1 run, another full toss and Tilak goes hard on the heave, ekes out an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls to mid-wicket
Rasikh Salam to Tim David, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, David pulls to deep square leg
There were some intense conversations had during the timeout. First Mark Boucher with the two batters then Hardik with David
Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, 1 run, low full toss around off, Tilak drills it along the ground to long-on
Rasikh Salam to Tim David, 1 run, that's an excellent over. Just 7 runs. Another low full toss, David closes the bat face and the leading edge rolls to extra cover
64 off 18. That over has definitely put Delhi in the ascendancy. Gives some breathing space for their bowlers in the final 3 overs. Mukesh to bowl this one. He's coming from round the wicket..
Mukesh Kumar [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Tim David, SIX, angles it outside off and David deposits it into the stands. He shuffles across and down the wicket, gets underneath the length ball and sends it sailing over long-on
Last ten team totals in IPL 2024 - nine of them in excess of 200 210/4 213/4 224/4 220/8 206/7 171/8 261/6 262/2 257/4 200/5 *
Back over the wicket

Mukesh Kumar to Tim David, FOUR, now one bounce and over the ropes. Once again a slot ball outside off, David moves across and drags the heave off the inner half, not off the middle but in the gap and beats deep mid-wicket

Mukesh Kumar to Tim David, SIX .. and the pendulum swings again. 16 off the first 3 balls and Mukesh is under pressure. He searches for the yorker but ends up dishing out a juicy full toss, David uses his power to muscle it over the wide long-on fence
Pant is up to the stumps now. He does not want David walking down the pitch

Mumbai review! David is given out LBW. He was happy to walk off but Tilak has asked him to challenge the decision. Mumbai do have both their reviews intact. This looked dead from the start. Nothing on UltraEdge either. Ball-tracking shows impact umpire's call and wickets hitting. OUT
Mukesh Kumar to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Mukesh Kumar to Tim David, out Lbw!! How smart was that move from Pant? He came up to the stumps and Delhi got their wicket. David was walking down the pitch to take on Mukesh and Pant coming up made him stop that. He tried to slog across the line by standing in the crease and missed the ball completely, struck low on the pad and impact was umpire's call. Mumbai don't lose a review but it is a big wicket that they have lost. Tim David lbw b Mukesh Kumar 37(17) [4s-2 6s-3]
Mohammad Nabi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Nabi, 1 run, full pitcher around off, Nabi drags it towards mid-wicket and it is only a single
Mukesh Kumar to Tilak Varma, SIX, that's a poor way to end the over. Full toss on leg-stump, Tilak sits down and helps it along the way over long leg
41 off 12. It is still doable. They need to just take it deep and then anything can happen under pressure.. Rasikh to continue

Rasikh Salam to Nabi, no run, yorker outside off, Nabi tries his best to reach it but can't lay a bat. He decides to review for a wide, but the ball was just inside the guideline. So they lose a review..
Rasikh Salam to Nabi, SIX, misses the yorker and that means it is right in the arc, Nabi gets under it and pumps it a long way down the ground
Rasikh Salam to Nabi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Nabi, out Caught by Shai Hope!! Third wicket for Rasikh. And he hasn't gone for many as well. This is a low full toss and Nabi does his best to get under it, slams it towards long-on and Hope takes a well-judged catch. Nabi c Shai Hope b Rasikh Salam 7(4) [6s-1]
Piyush Chawla, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Rasikh Salam to Chawla, SIX, this is just incredible. Even Chawla is smashing 'em from the get go. Pant has a smile on his face. Rasikh misses the yorker and feeds it in the slot, Chawla thumps it straight and watches it sail over the rope
Rasikh Salam to Chawla, byes, 1 run, nails the yorker outside off, Chawla cannot squeeze it out and Tilak calls him for a quick single, dives in to make his ground

Rasikh Salam to Tilak Varma, 3 runs, this is the best result Mumbai could have hoped for - three runs. Low full toss outside off, Tilak drives in front of square and Fraser-McGurk had a lot of ground to cover, he gets there with a dive and saves the boundary, but Tilak will retain strike
25 needed off the last over. Tilak has managed to hold on to the strike. Mukesh has been given the onus to defend. Pant has removed his right glove so he can be ready for a throw.
Have Delhi won it? Looks like Tilak has been run-out. The home team are celebrating. Tilak is down on his haunches. He knows he's short of the crease. OUT
Mukesh Kumar to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Mukesh Kumar to Tilak Varma, out Tilak Varma Run Out!! 1 run completed. That's a good way to start the last over for Delhi. They have sent back the set batter and the only one who had a chance of taking them over the line. Slower ball around leg-stump, Tilak heaves it towards deep square leg, the ball lands in front of the incoming fielder and he decides to go for the second, Sumit sends a good throw to Pant and he lights up the stumps, Tilak puts in the dive but that was not enough to save him. Tilak Varma run out (Sumit Kumar/Pant) 63(32) [4s-4 6s-4]
Luke Wood, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Mukesh Kumar to Wood, 2 runs, that would have been a stunner from JFM. Slower ball and Wood miscues the heave, the ball goes straight up and JFM races in from deep mid-wicket, he puts in the dive and gets there but is not able to hold on
Mukesh Kumar to Wood, SIX, is there still life left in this game? Wood gets hold of this slower ball and heaves it towards deep mid-wicket, there's enough wood on that for the ball to clear the rope
Mukesh Kumar to Wood, 1 run, slogs across the line and does not get the desired connection, just a single
Mukesh Kumar to Chawla, FOUR, off-pace delivery outside off, Chawla waits and chips it over extra cover, he clears the infield and picks up the boundary
Mukesh Kumar to Chawla, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Chawla, out Caught by Shai Hope!! Delhi Capitals win by 10 runs. Mukesh too ends up with a 3-fer. It was a high full toss, Chawla swings through the line and gets it high on the bat, the ball skies towards long-on and Hope makes no mistake. There was a check for a possible no-ball but the ball was below the waist. Chawla c Shai Hope b Mukesh Kumar 10(4) [4s-1 6s-1]

19:40 Local Time, 14:10 GMT: Phew! Another humdinger of a game. When is a contest really over these days? It is not over when Rohit, Kishan and SKY are sent back within the powerplay. It is not over when Hardik and Wadhera depart in the same over. It is not over when Mumbai's most powerful batter - Tim David - falls in the 18th over. It is only over when the last ball is bowled. That is the confidence and self belief of every batter in this edition. Tilak Varma was the standout for Mumbai, he played the anchor as well as the aggressor and with little more support, he would have taken the game away from Delhi. Rasikh Dar was the pick for the home side, he came on as an impact sub and picked up 3 for 34 in this high-scoring affair while the rest went for plenty. In the end it was his spell of four overs which made the difference. Stick around for the presentations..

Hardik Pandya | MI Captain: This game is becoming more and more closer. It (the difference) used to be a couple of overs, now it’s becoming a couple of balls. Because of the kind of games and how the bowlers are under pressure, we backed ourselves to do it. If I had to pick something out, we could have taken a couple of more chances in the middle overs. The left-handers could have probably gone after Axar a little bit, it’s something we missed out in terms of game awareness. It was quite amazing the way he (Fraser-McGurk) batted, he took calculated risks, he played the field really well. It shows the fearlessness of youth. (If he would’ve done something different at the toss) Not really.

Rasikh Dar (translated from Hindi): It was tough as the wicket was flat but we had planned and the coach had prepared us. I'm trying to fulfil the team's demands and I held my nerve. This is a confidence game and the more you have, the better it is. We plan together, do it before the game as well. [on Pant standing up to the seamers] It was a good move and a wicket fell next ball, Pant tells us to deliver as you do and I will come up to the stumps.
